<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>Zend_Form_Element_File#setRequired should require at least one of multi files, but it does all of them uploaded.</p>

<p>Zend_Form_Element_File#isValid returns false 
When you call setMultiFile($count) and setRequired(true) for Zend_Form_Element_File
and you upload one file or files less than $count.</p>

<p>I think setRequired should check if one or some files are uploaded only.
Otherwise you do not have a way to create file elements that you need to upload at least one file.
Regarding the file count, you can use the Count validator.</p>

<p>$file = new Zend_Form_Element_File('file');
$file-&gt;setDestination($upload_destination_path)
-&gt;setRequired(true)
-&gt;setMultiFile($max_file_count)
-&gt;addValidator('Count', false, array('min' =&gt; $min_file_count, 'max' =&gt; $max_file_count));</p>

